      <h2 class="section-title">When it&#8217;s worth seeing a doctor</h2>
      <p>There&#8217;s no need to wait for it to become a bigger problem before asking for help. A doctor can usually identify likely contributors from a short conversation and a few simple checks.</p>
      <p>Because ED can sometimes be an early sign of heart or vascular disease, getting it checked is also a useful way to look after your overall health &#8212; not only your sex life.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="signs-visual">
      <h3>Book a consultation if:</h3>
      <ul class="signs-list">
        <li><div class="signs-check">&#10003;</div>It&#8217;s happened regularly for several weeks or more</li>
        <li><div class="signs-check">&#10003;</div>It&#8217;s affecting your confidence or relationship</li>
        <li><div class="signs-check">&#10003;</div>You also have diabetes, high blood pressure or heart disease</li>
        <li><div class="signs-check">&#10003;</div>It started suddenly or alongside a new medication</li>
        <li><div class="signs-check">&#10003;</div>You&#8217;re simply unsure why it&#8217;s happening</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
